The paper discusses the use of microservices in the context of a complex application scenario, specifically in the domain of community health care. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category, as it focuses on the design and development of software systems. Additionally, the use of microservices implies a distributed architecture, which could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The paper also discusses the use of resilient and autonomous services, which could be related to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. The application scenario involves the Internet of Things (IoT) and community health care, which could fall under the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Finally, the paper discusses the modelling of a complex system, which could be related to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
